title: At (5-2), UMD is No. 20 in AFCA II Poll
text:
At (5-2), UMD is No. 20 in AFCA II Poll 
By Zach Schneider At (5-2), UMD is No. 20 in AFCA II Poll October 19, 2015 Updated Oct 19, 2015 at 1:30 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) football team moved up one spot to No. 20 in this week's American Football Coaches' Association (AFCA) Division II poll, which was released on Monday afternoon. 
The Bulldogs beat Mary 45-0 this past Saturday afternoon, moving to (5-2) overall this season. The two teams to beat UMD, MSU-Mankato and Sioux Falls, are ranked No. 1 and No. 5, respectively. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
For full results of this week's AFCA II poll, click here. 
UMD will be back at home Oct. 24, hosting Minnesota-Crookston at 1:05 p.m. at Malosky Stadium. That game will be aired live in the Northland on the My 9 Sports Network.
